I would consider revisiting a Tokyo sequal in hopes of buying time to find a director and focus to get FF with the full cast back on track. text: Sadly. All went wrong. The point of Fast and Furious is seriusly twisted right now. So you letting Han's murderer to be a friend?! Bullshit. I miss pure street racing, little bit of action, I miss the movie that was inspirational to gather up family and put them in the first place. You may see a lot of people saying this movie will be good, but no...60% of those people haven't watched first 4 movies of the franchise. Someone is destroying Fast and Furious, and between that, our hearts. Remember this: *“I live my life a quarter mile at a time. Nothing else matters: not the mortgage, not the store, not my team and all their bullshit. For those ten seconds or less, I’m free.”*...or this: *"I don't have friends, I have family."*? I'm dissapointed, the Fast and Furious culture changed me into a full petrolhead and I live my life by that. And on top of that, without Paul, there is no explanation to make more movies, goddamit! I remember watching first Fast and Furious, being that kid freaking out when seeing that first scene with Brian riding his green Eclipse...and now...I'm sorry, but I'm not watching this. It sure do breaks my heart, but it's the way it is. FnF7 should've been the last one. :/

text: I seriously cannot believe these films are still being made. I saw the first one and thought I was hot shit for dissing it and even saw the second one because who gives a shit I was on a high school movie date. I stopped watching them...but then they kept making them. Then they made even more of them.  Every single time I was baffled and confused as to why these movies were still being made. I still am. This franchise should have died 10 fucking years ago. But they just kept shitting them out. And surprisingly, they got better. They got  better review and better box office returns and better world of mouth and I was like are you fucking kidding me these Fast and the Furious movies are an actual legitimate franchise that makes shitloads of money?!  So I gave them another shot and sure enough I liked the more recent flicks over the older ones.  Never though I'd see the day.  Justin Lin knows what the fuck he is doing and does it WELL. Watched Star Trek Beyond last night and aside from the stupid ass motorcycle scenes he fucking nailed it. I'll be surprised though if this franchise can survive both Paul Walker and Justin Lin no longer being involved. I was wrong before. prove me wrong again.

This is the only explanation as to why Brian wouldn't come in and take dom down himself. Obviously this would be borderline disrespectful and would probably piss off a lot of fans. text: As an action film and sequel to the seventh film this looks pretty awesome. I have to admit i didn't join the fan base til Furious 7. These films were sort of off my radar as i'm not really a racing enthusiast. I didn't really engage with the franchise til a friend of mine dragged me to the cinema in 2014 and on an action movie, humor and emotional level I enjoyed that very much and then i went back and watched the first 6 and really enjoyed those too. That's probably why I'm not too concerned with the less street racing more action approach. In terms of an exciting and unpredictable place of taking the franchise this looks good to me. Even if they are mainly vehicular mayhem and action nowadays, you gotta admit that they do what they do spectacularly and to still keep the emotional core of the family center stage that's impressive for an action franchise for it to have that much on it's mind. Hell I'll watch it, just for the action but the drama looks pretty intense too. Glad Mr Nobody and Statham are back, they were cool in 7.

text: Legit garbage. Let's be honest here: The only reason anyone would want to see this, is to prove that they were right about how he'll really turn out to be a good person, but was pretending to be bad all along to get that Charlize's character out of the way. Other than that, why would anyone wanna see this movie? They really should have ended it with the last one. That movie ended in a way which imo, was a good farewell to all the characters that are still alive, along with the series as a whole.   Then, we're told they're making another one which at first sounded awesome and cool, but by looking at this trailer, it's clear they've ran out of ideas and legit had to make Dom the bad guy to keep the story going? It sure the hell wasn't because it sounded like a great idea on paper. There were so many ways they could have gone with this, and they picked such a cheap and unoriginal idea to make yet another movie of the series.   But, sadly enough, this movie will sell well because it's a series that everyone loves (including me). Just don't like where they've went with this one. But I'm sure we'll have a better idea, or not, of why they picked this route for when it comes out next year.

text: This has long turned into a loony tunes cartoon.   I loved how down to earth Tokyo Drift was even half way around the world it really moved me, even for an action flick it was great and I was hoping the following FnF films would follow that direction but they just kept drifting back towards Fast and Furious 1, and even worse, 2 Fast 2 Furious like calamities.  Just entirely takes you out of the moment and the immersion but what ever, it'll be a fun flick to watch but would have been better off had they kept the tokyo drift direction and feel.  Don't get me wrong, it'll be a lot of fun.  But they could have had the same fun cars, same fun action but a bit more down to earth (that's an understatement) and had a good flowing story to go along with it.  Stories a joke now, but it does look like a fun action flick either way.  It doesn't really matter because there's really no redeeming 2 fast 2 furious anyway.

Then Fast 6 comes along, and we think, ok, tanks planes, reuniting with enemies, getting the old life back, FINAL resolutions, no longer criminals, etc. SHOULD'VE STOPPED THERE. But no, then you make another, and loose the best actor along the way, but sure, you manage to pull it into a decent movie.......why must you keep going? You're turning this into guns and shooting, when it used to be a car/heist/street racing/criminal redemption movie.....

text: I feel so honored to be the first comment. All of my hard work and dedication has paid off. Getting the first comment has been a dream of mine for many years, and I would like to thank those who have helped me along the way. First and foremost i would like to thank god for giving me this opportunity. Next i would like to thank my parents. I want to thank my friend Peter Griffin for being really skinny and always there for me. I would also like to thank my pet tadpole for surviving for over a week. Next i would like to thank the squirrel that lives in my backyard for climbing trees because that gives me inspiration that i need to get through the day. This is a special moment in my life and i would like to thank any of my unmentioned friends and family that have helped me along the way. This moment will be a moment that I will never forget. I just remembered a few other people i would like to thank; Abraham Lincoln, the fish I caught in the third grade, my light in my room because i wouldn’t be able to see the keyboard without it, the internet for letting me go on Youtube, my house because without it i would be homeless, and last but not least i would like to thank all the people out there that actually took time out of their day to read this. I cannot stress how much of a big deal to me this is. I have been trying to be the first on a post for years, but that has not been possible until this amazing day. Hopefully my good luck will continue, but this is undoubtedly a rare occasion. If you asked me how I did this, I would say, you can achieve anything you set your mind on. To all the kids out there reading this, I would like to tell them to follow their dreams. Being the first is truly amazing, thank you everyone.

I almost went homeless, like actual homeless about 4 times towards the end of summer and 2 months of fall. I lost weight due to not having money, went weak, lost motivation from the gym. I used to be jacked. I had stopped making youtube videos for a while too. BUT MY LIFE HAS turned around, I work at an awesome place nearby. I have a better car than I did. I am going to the gym again and I've grown 2k subs in two months from pickin back up. Long story short: If you've been having a shitty year or going through tough times, just remember things get better. AND YOU'RE AWESOME ! That's pretty much it honestly. haha

text: Not gonna lie. When I first saw the title and thumb nail, I was thinking this was going to be one big ripoff. But as the trailer started playing out, I began to get excited. I think I enjoyed the trailer because of the simple fact that I got to see majority of characters I grew up with again. Tyrese is by far my favorite and I love the Rock's dry humor.   Aside from the overuse of explosions in a TRAILER, I'm looking forward to this. I also love the Dom twist despite how 'cliche' and 'played out' it is. Face it, if any other character had turned we would find a way to justify it but with Dom everyone is asking "Why Dom when he preaches faithfully about family?" Maybe the plot is obvious, maybe it's not. Either way, spend the money to see or don't.

text: Dom is the bloodline of the family - he is literally behind it all and for that, we love him as a character. I know it seems brilliant to make him turn on his family as it will add for HUGE suspense and a plot twist, but honestly there is too strong of an attraction to the fans and Don that makes this franchise great. His connection to the Fast and Furious family is what made this series so unique and appreciable. Now, Dom turning on his family (even if he comes back to them) completely defeats the purpose of the series and contradicts what the fans love completely. I miss the old Fast and Furious where they would drive Tuners, race and do jobs because they loved it. Now, there's always SOMETHING that comes in the way. There is something that ALWAYS interferes. Don't get me wrong, I still like Fast 7 and 6, and I will probably enjoy this one nonetheless, but my heart will always be with the original five Fast and Furious movies (Fast Five was my favourite). Does anyone else agree?

text: The first was fun entertainment with simple but very likeable characters. The second was weak but still kinda okayish. Contrary to many others I really like the third one. The setting was nice and the Han character is one of the best in the series - besides Brain and Dom of course. The Fourth was pretty solid and almost as good as the first. They took a terrible turn with the fifth movie. It looks like they picked the worst movie so far in the series - the second - and said: hey let's do this again, but without the car tuning scene stuff. While not being a total letdown it didn't felt like a F&F movie at all. But instead of going back to the roots they are just riding the same horse over and over again. Each and every F&F movie since then seems to be like the fifth but its get stupider with each instalment. The sixth was almost unbearably stupid. I watched the 7th only because I wanted to see how they deal with Pauls death. I wish I didn't. Unless some wonder happens I'll pass on the 8th and all the crap that's probably about to come with the F&F label.

text: People should stop hating on the new fast and furious movies just because Paul isn't here with us.  I mean, I loved Paul Walker.  I idolized him and I still do.  When he passed, it was like losing a family member.  All of my friends started getting angry that Fast and Furious movies will suck because Paul is not here, but that is just because people are jumping on the bandwagon.  The producers of F&F can't just bring Paul back, even though it would make all of the world's problems end if they did.  But instead of hating on this series, we should appreciate how far it has come, and not hate on the fact that the movies aren't completely street-racing based anymore.  We should come together as a community of F&F watchers, and appreciate the good things about these movies.    R.I.P Paul.  Miss you a lot bro. :(

text: I think it needs to be said that a lot of what ends up in movie trailers is also what hit the cutting room floor. I've seen plenty of trailers that had scenes or shots that weren't even in the final cut of the movie. While you're right that these are continuity issues keep in mind that they likely won't show up in the cinema version. Also, with regard to the 30mm canon being shot from the roof of the SUV, it is very likely that the spent rounds were added for affect as it doesn't look like the canon is even dispensing any spent rounds. That and the fact that they get thrown further than what the edge of the vehicle is and the vehicle is moving at a high rate of speed so they would end up behind the point of release not in front. They are also very hot. So the real thing would have likely scorched the top of the vehicle and the actor.

(They walk towards the table and you hear Letty saying) L: Dom? Why does Brian owes you a 10 second car?    (Dom looks at the horizon, not responding to the question, then turns to Letty smiling, takes her hand and they make their way to the table. text: #eapp2017 Another great movie to watch this year. Fate of the Furious, the sequel of the Fast 7. This movie is about family and cars just like the previous Fast and the Furious movies but the trailer of this sequel showed the betrayal of Dom. The special effects was wonderful; you will see it in every scene but watch the scene with the submarine and cool cars. The storyline was unpredictable; I thought Dom betrayed the team because of Cypher but it was not. I'm not going to spoil that's why I'm not going to tell it. I felt the goosebumps in the end (spoiler alert) because Dom named his child Bryan. That made me teary. All in all, this sequel is fantastic due to the production, the settings, story, special effects and of course, cool cars. Thumbs up.
